# Pharmax Enterprise Pharmacy OS

We are building a modern enterprise pharmacy operating system inspired by LifeFile.

The platform must support:

- RX intake
- Typing
- PV1 pharmacist verification
- Filling
- Final pharmacist verification
- Shipping release
- Zebra vial label printing
- Barcode scanner validation
- Lot and inventory traceability
- EasyPost-style tracking
- Custom operational buckets
- Clinic/team/user isolation
- Billing and invoicing
- Complex reporting
- SLA timers and emergency buckets
- User productivity reports
- Secure patient/provider/order search
- Full audit history

Preferred architecture:

Next.js frontend
→ thin API routes
→ auth/RBAC/context
→ command handlers
→ workflow engine
→ domain services
→ repositories
→ PostgreSQL transaction
→ order update
→ queue/bucket movement
→ order event
→ audit log
→ command log
→ event outbox
→ workers process side effects

Use:

- Next.js, React, TypeScript, Tailwind
- PostgreSQL
- Prisma
- Redis or Valkey
- Background workers
- S3-compatible storage
- Modular nternals

Do not build route-heavy business logic.
Do not build premature microservices.
